#### [NEW] src/models/Session.ts
Mongoose model for refresh tokens in MongoDB with **strict TTL auto-expiry**:

```typescript
// Schema fields:
//   userId:       String (ref to PG user id)
//   refreshToken: String (hashed)
//   userAgent:    String (device info)
//   ipAddress:    String
//   expiresAt:    Date   ‚Üê TTL index target
//   createdAt:    Date

// MongoDB TTL index ‚Äî tokens auto-delete when expiresAt is reached
sessionSchema.index({ expiresAt: 1 }, { expireAfterSeconds: 0 });
```

This ensures expired refresh tokens are automatically purged by MongoDB's background TTL monitor (~every 60s), keeping the collection lean with zero manual cleanup.

